Project: Pathologies baseline

Description: Automatic Voice Disorder Detection (Binary and Multiclass classification) 
             Features: Opensmile (Compare2016) 
             Classifier: SVM (sklearn)

Copyright: Vivolab
Contact: Dayana Ribas-dribas@unizar.es
Date: May/2022

Content: 
executables: bin
source code: src
audio files: data/audio
features in csv: data/features
lists: data/lst
results: data/result


Usage: run_baseline.py list_path kfold audio_type_gender
       audio_type (Saarbruecken(SVD)): a_n, aiu, phrases, multi_a_n, multi_aiu, multi_phrases
       audio_type (AVFAD): aiu, phrases, read, spontaneous, multi_aiu, multi_phrases, multi_read, multi_spontaneous
       gender: both, hombres, mujeres

Example Binary Classification:
> python bin/run_baseline.py  data/lst/Saarbruecken 5 phrase_both
> python bin/run_baseline.py  data/lst/AVFAD 5 phrase_both

Example Multiclass Classification: 
> python bin/run_baseline.py  data/lst/AVFAD 5 multi_phrase_both

Example Compute and Save features:
> python bin/run_features_opensmile.py data/audio/Saarbruecken data/features/Saarbruecken

